             \begin {tikzpicture}[diagram]
               \SpliceDiagramSquare {
                nw = A'',
                nw/style = pullback,
                ne = B'',
                sw = A,
                se = B,
                north =  \varepsilon _{g'},
                west =  f ^{*} (g'),
                west/node/style = {right},
                south = f,
                east = g',
              }
               \node  [above left of = nw] (a') {$A'$};
               \draw  [->,morphism,bend right] (a') to node[swap] {$ f ^{*} (g)$} (sw);
               \draw  [->,morphism,bend left] (a') to node {$ \alpha \varepsilon _{g}$} (ne);
               \draw  [->,morphism,exists] (a') to node[desc] {$ f ^{*} ( \alpha )$} (nw);
             \end {tikzpicture}



          Thus, \varepsilon _{g'} \Sigma _{f}( f ^{*} ( \alpha )) =  \varepsilon _{g'} f ^{*} ( \alpha ) =  \alpha \varepsilon _{g} as required.

An object is a morphism g in { \mathcal { C } _{/{ B }}} with codomain f.





